Topic: Chemistry (10th Level – Railway Focus)
1️⃣ Clear Theory (Easy Language)

Railway Chemistry mostly includes:

Matter (Solid, Liquid, Gas)

Atoms & Molecules

Acids, Bases & Salts

Metals & Non-metals

Chemical Reactions

Periodic Table basics

👉 Questions are mostly:

Fact-based

Definition-based

Very direct

2️⃣ Important Concepts
🔹 Matter

Solid → Fixed shape & volume

Liquid → Fixed volume only

Gas → No fixed shape or volume

🔹 Atomic Number

Number of protons in nucleus

🔹 pH Scale

Acid → pH < 7

Neutral → pH = 7

Base → pH > 7

🔹 Common Chemicals

H₂O → Water

NaCl → Common salt

CO₂ → Carbon dioxide

HCl → Hydrochloric acid

🔹 Metals

Good conductors of heat & electricity

Malleable & ductile

🧠 Quick Tricks (Railway Favourite)

Remember common chemical formulas

pH value questions are common

Metal vs Non-metal properties asked frequently

